{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"36d08f20-e6d8-4d3f-82d8-3d5fd7d71976","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** in MSTest v3. You need to migrate the settings into a `.runsettings` file. Here's what each piece maps to:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` property | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code Coverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| `AssemblyResolution` / deployment | No longer needed — MSTest v3 handles this natively |\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` file and update the project:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_7q4OAyesXOcgRVzF3AIwKz","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_HYAPXt83prchtpA2BQJLPS","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dc7d952012c547a299292b37975e7706/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.VanguardDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-dc7d952012c547a299292b37975e7706/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"b193e8ec-c21d-4eef-9a3d-2d9c88c475c7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n1. A `.testsettings` file with:\n   - Assembly resolution / test deployment config\n   - A `TestTimeout` of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n   - A code coverage data collector\n\n2. A `.csproj` that already references MSTest 3.8.0\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The equivalent configuration should be done via a `.runsettings` file and MSTest attributes/properties.\n\nLet me explain the migration path:\n\n1. **TestTimeout**: In MSTest v3, you can set this via `[Timeout]` attribute on individual tests, or globally via `.runsettings` with `<TestTimeout>` in the `<MSTest>` section, or via `MSTest.TestTimeout` property.\n\n\n2. **Code Coverage Data Collector**: This goes into `.runsettings` under `<DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly Resolution / Test Deployment**: In MSTest v3, deployment is handled differently. The `useLoadContext` setting and `AssemblyResolution` are no longer needed as MSTest v3 handles this natively.\n4. The `.testsettings` file reference should be removed and replaced with a `.runsettings` file.\n\nNow I'll create a `.runsettings` file that handles the timeout configuration, code coverage collection, and removes the deprecated deployment settings.","outputTokens":763,"requestId":"63DC:34550C:3BCCDCD:41FA864:6A02FA50"},"id":"661dcda8-352d-43c8-a1ed-f2a25bf6bfde","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:01:07.506Z","parentId":"55810fa3-2213-4103-a59f-8364f0198127"}
